<F P=101> PAKISTAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poppy Crops Destroyed in Bajaur </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3101163894 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3101163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A high-level meeting in Peshawar was informed today 
that poppy crops covering 2,090 kanals [approximately 289 acres] 
of land were destroyed in Bajaur Agency during the current 
season. Acting Governor Major General, retired, Khurshid Ali 
Khan, who chaired the meeting, directed that the law enforcement 
agencies make all-out efforts to eliminate poppy cultivation and 
heroin laboratories. 

</TEXT>

