<F P=100> AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> NAMIBIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Drug Enforcement Bureau Reviews 1993 Seizures, Arrests </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB3001072794 Windhoek THE NAMIBIAN in English 24 Jan 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> MB3001072794 </F>
<F P=104>  Windhoek THE NAMIBIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Tyappa Namutewa] </F>
  [Text] The Drug Enforcement Bureau of the Namibian Police 
[Nampol] last year confiscated a total of 3,262kg of Cannabis 
valued at N$[Namibian dollars]10,426,362 and arrested 366 people 
in connection with drug smuggling. The police revealed this on 
Friday following a media enquiry. 
  Apart from the massive Cannabis haul, 75,439 Mandrax tablets 
valued at N$2,263,170 were seized. 
  Nampol said most of the drugs had been confiscated through 
the "excellent assistance of the public," while others had been 
seized in joint operations with neighbouring countries. 
  In 1993 Cocaine valued at more than N$1.3 million had also 
been confiscated. 
  Overall there had been 242 cases involving drugs during 1993 
and 366 people had been arrested of whom 37 had been foreigners. 
The police again warned the public about the danger of drugs 
and urged people to report any cases of drug smuggling to the 
nearest police station. 

</TEXT>

