<F P=100> AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> SWAZILAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Destroy Mandrax, Marijuana Worth More Than 3 Million Rands </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2601193594 Mbabane Radio Swaziland Network in English 1600 
GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2601193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mbabane Radio Swaziland Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Police today destroyed exhibits in the form of 
drugs--mandrax tablets and dagga [marijuana]--at the Usuthu Pulp 
blast furnace. The police public relations officer, Inspector 
Azariah Ndzimandze, said the drugs had been in the possession of 
police from 1990 to 1993. The total number of tablets were 
18,006,064 with a street value of over 3 million emalangeni, and 
there were 195 bags of dagga with a street value of 199,500 
emalangeni. Inspector Ndzimandze added that the drugs were not 
destroyed earlier because some of the exhibits were pending 
cases with the courts. 

</TEXT>

