<F P=100> EAST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Svilengrad Court Sentences Macedonian, Polish Heroin Smugglers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701131994 Sofia BTA in English 2121 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2701131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Today"--BTA lead] </F>
  [Excerpt] Sofia, January 26 (BTA) -- The Svilengrad 
District Court sentenced Erfan Erfi of Macedonia to three years 
and eight months imprisonment for attempting to smuggle 10.230 
kg of unrefined heroin in an Opel Manta on September 4, 1993. 
Jaroslaw Nedzulka, a Polish national caught in an attempt to 
carry 10.430 kg of heroin illegally across the border in an 
Audi, received a six year prison sentence. Andrzej Dromond, who 
travelled together with Nedzulka, was acquitted. The drug 
traffickers will also pay fines, and their cars are confiscated. 

</TEXT>

