<F P=100> WEST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Drug Dealers Arrested; Cannabis Resin Seized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2901201094 Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG in German 29 Jan 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> AU2901201094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Hashish Deals Busted: Two Men </F>
Imprisoned"] 
  [Excerpt] The investigators of the drug group of the Lower 
Austrian Criminal Investigation Department have found out about 
flourishing deals with cannabis resin. Nikolaus S. (29) from 
Vienna-Hernals is said to have smuggled 80 to 100 kg of the 
"Tscharas" type of the drug from India to Austria in the past 
eight years. The man is currently in India. Alfred H. (37) and 
Wilhelm B. (38) from Vienna-Fuenfhaus were imprisoned. It is 
assumed that they distributed the drugs. 
  During a search of Wilhelm B.'s apartment, 2,850 grams of 
cannabis resin were seized. Alfred H. is suspected of having 
daily procured five to seven buyers of heroin for several 
distributors in 1992 and 1993. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

