<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> RUSSIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chechen President Calls for Public Executions of Drug Dealers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3101143994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1036 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3101143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Groznyy, 31 Jan (CHECHENPRESS-TASS) -- "Anyone who 
is peddling drugs in the republic, either for profit or at the 
instructions of the secret services, must be physically 
eliminated," Chechen President Dzhokhar Dudayev said in Groznyy 
at a regular sitting of the republic's Security Council. 
Dudayev's statement was released today by the CHECHENPRESS 
agency. The Chechen president's opinion is that "with the 
connivance of local authorities and law enforcement bodies, drug 
addiction has reached such proportions that it threatens the 
nation's gene pool." 
  The CHECHENPRESS agency reports that the procurator general 
"has been instructed to draft a law on applying the death 
penalty to drug dealers." 
  According to Dudayev, "As a beginning, it is necessary to 
hold a few public executions," CHECHENPRESS reports. 

</TEXT>

