<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Antinarcotics Operations for 21 January-3 February </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402043194 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402043194 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
fileworthy reports on antinarcotics operations in countries 
covered by FBIS London Bureau from 21 January to 3 February. 
Sources are given at the end of each report. 
<H5>  Italy </H5>
  Carabinieri from the Caserta (southern Italy) Anti-Mafia 
Investigative Directorate discovered a cocaine refinery at 
Coppola Pineta Mare on the coast near Unizzio. Sixty kilograms 
of cocaine were seized and five people were arrested. (Rome RAI 
Due Television Network in Italian 1045 GMT 26 Jan) 
<H5>  Kyrgyzstan </H5>
  A cargo of marijuana was detained at the airport of 
Kyrgyzstan's capital, Bishkek. Six and a half kilograms of 
marijuana were hidden in a defunct refrigerator in the waiting 
hall. The border guards found it just before the departure of a 
foreign plane. (Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 
0800 GMT 1 Jan) 
<H5>  Spain </H5>
  Three people have been arrested in La Linea de la Concepcion 
(near Gibraltar). They are being accused of belonging to a drug 
trafficking network after they were found in the possession of 
149 kilos of hashish. (Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 
1600 GMT 29 Jan) 

</TEXT>

