<H3> <TI>   Italian Drug Trafficker Faces Extradition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0202170194 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1800 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0202170194 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Diego Fajardo from the "NTC News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Italian drug trafficker Roberto Panunzzi is 
currently in a DIJIN [Judicial Police and Investigations 
Directorate] cell in Santa Fe de Bogota. He was captured in 
Medellin and will be extradited to his country in a few hours. 
Panunzzi faces two charges in Colombia: one for drug 
trafficking and another for forgery, because he was carrying a 
personal identification card, a driver's license, and a 
safe-conduct issued in the name of Francisco Oliva Gomez, a 
native of Florida, Valle Department. 
  [Begin Colonel Teodoro Campos recording] We have not caught 
everyone, but we have the most important ones in Colombian, 
English, and Italian jails. [end recording] 
  Roberto Panunzzi is the sixth person captured in Colombia as 
part of Operation Angelo II. Italy has offered Colombia 18 
billion pesos to assist in the war on drugs. 

</TEXT>

