<H3> <TI>   SAN Source Cited on Drug Transshipment Locations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0102210394 Panama City EL PANAMMA AMERICA in Spanish 31 
Jan 94 p 8C </F>

<F P=103> PA0102210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City EL PANAMMA AMERICA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jose Manuel Diaz C.] </F>
  [Text] Members of drug cartels are using the Pacific coast 
area between the Azuero Peninsula and Punta Burica, in Chiriqui 
Province, to drop packages containing drugs which are later 
transported ashore, a source at the National Air Service (SAN) 
has reported. 
  According to the source, authorities constantly receive 
reports of fishermen and residents on drug shipments that are 
brought ashore. The source added that this kind of activity has 
also been reported in several provinces, such as Chiriqui, 
Colon, and Veraguas. He said that in the Atlantic sector, boats 
are using the island of Escudo de Veraguas for illegal 
activities due to the lack of surveillance. 
  The source stated that the SAN is constantly conducting 
operations in the most vulnerable points for this kind of 
activity, but the lack of aircraft and resources prevents them 
from maintaining constant surveillance. 
  However, the source said he did not know whether the town of 
Viento Frio in Colon Province is being used for the trafficking 
of drugs. He indicated that so far SAN authorities on the 
Atlantic coast do not have reports on the use of this location 
as a point for transshipping narcotics. Recently, residents of 
this town reported the presence of boats that drop drug 
packages, which are later picked up by persons who sell 
narcotics. 
  During 1993, the authorities conducted several 
counternarcotics operations in the Provinces of Chiriqui and 
Bocas del Toro, which led to the arrest of several people 
allegedly involved in drug contraband. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

