<H3> <TI>   Police in Chiang Mai Seize 52.7 Kg of Heroin, Arrest 2 Chinese Men </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0202021094 Bangkok THE NATION in English 2 Feb 94 p A2 </F>
<F P=103> BK0202021094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok THE NATION </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Police have arrested two Chinese men in Chiang Mai 
for allegedly trafficking in 52.7 kilos of heroin, Pol Gen 
Chaovalit Yodmanee told a press conference yesterday. 
  The suspects from Yunnan, identified as Pakasit sae Yang, 
alias Kwo-ong, 35, and Sumeth Meengarm, alias Ar-fu, 32, were 
arrested on Monday at a Chiang Mai department store along with 
the 52.7 kilos of heroin. 
  Police said the two admitted that they had been hired to 
transport the drug, which was concealed in candle wax, to a 
dealer in Hat Yai, Songkhla province. 
  Sumeth allegedly confessed to police that he had 
successfully 
delivered heroin twice before and received Bt80,000 in return, 
while Pakasit allegedly said he had done the job four times 
previously. 
  Police said the two refused to identify who was behind the 
operation, admitting only that there were a number of people 
involved. 

