<F P=101> INDIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Three Kenyan Women Arrested With 9 Kg of Heroin at Sahar Airport </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0180 Bombay THE TIMES OF INDIA in English 10 Dec 93 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0180 </F>
<F P=104>  Bombay THE TIMES OF INDIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Bombay, December 9--Customs officers of the marine 
and preventive wing yesterday arrested three Kenyan women at 
Sahar airport after nine kgs of heroin, worth about Rs 27 crore 
in international markets, was discovered in their baggage. 
  The officials said the drug had been concealed in tins of 
milk powder, coffee, mashed potato, and orange juice in the 
luggage of Victoria Muthen Katnu. The names of her companions 
were given as Hadija Ndope Saidai and Naima Nyakinywa. All three 
were scheduled to fly to Nairobi by an early morning Kenyan 
Airways flight yesterday. 
  Subsequently, the customs officers searched the Bandra 
residence of Dr Kalu Ojiewu, the alleged supplier of the heroin. 
Dr Ojiewu reportedly attempted to escape by leaping off the 
balcony of his first floor flat at plot number 51 on 29th road, 
but was overpowered and held. 
  It is believed that the narcotics were procured by Dr Ojiewu 
from a source in Rajasthan. 

</TEXT>

