<F P=101> IRAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Six Killed, 241 Kg of Narcotics Seized During Operation in Kerman </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102201494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0102201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a successful operation the combatants of the 41st 
Sarallah Division of the Guards Corps Ground Forces smashed six 
convoys carrying narcotics in the general vicinity of Andujerd 
in Kerman and impassable heights. 
  According to a report from the Guards Corps, in the 
operation 
codenamed the Birth Anniversary of Mahdi, God speed his advent, 
brave personnel of the forces of Islam, in a clash lasting for 
several hours, surrounded the convoys of 'Isa, Javad, and 
Shamshir Shahbakhsh and three other convoys of the Shahbakhsh 
group and dealt them heavy blows. 
  According to this report, in the clash, which was executed 
using the element of surprise, the combatants of the 41st 
Sarallah Division of the Guards Corps Ground Forces, with the 
cooperation of the brave personnel of Kerman Army Aviation 
personnel, killed six merchants of death and wounded 10 others. 
The forces of Islam seized 32 sacks of narcotics weighing 241 
kg, five vehicles, 30 motorcycles, and 40 light weapons with 
ammunition in the operation. 

</TEXT>

