<F P=101> IRAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Miscreants' Tied to Drug Trafficker Kidnap Three Soldiers Near Zahedan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402153994 Tehran IRNA in English 1517 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Zahedan (Sistan-Baluchestan), Feb. 4, IRNA -- A 
number of armed miscreants blocked the Zahedan-Zabol road in 
Tasuki region in this southeastern province last night killing 
four passengers of a passing bus and looting other passengers. 
  According to the local IRNA correspondent the miscreants 
have 
kidnapped three soldiers retuning to Zahedan from leave. 
  The provincial law enforcement official rushing to the scene 
immediately mobilised all resources to track down the 
miscreants, resulting in the arrest of two of bandits along with 
weapons and several rounds of ammunition. 
  The panic-stricken passengers of the bus were being 
questioned on details of the attack. 
  A law enforcement official told IRNA that the miscreants 
were 
agents of a notorious drug trafficking gang leader known as 
'Hamid Nahtani. 
  Nahtani leads an international gang which uses Iran soil as 
a 
transit route to smuggle drugs to Europe. 
  At the moment, said the official, all roads leading to 
Zahedan have been reopened and the security forces are keeping a 
vigilance. A special group was also trying to track down the 
rest of the miscreants, he added. 
  The smugglers had blocked the Khash-Zahedan, Kerman-Zahedan 
and Zabol-Zahedan roads in the past weeks several times looting 
people's properties. 

</TEXT>

