Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Katy Turner] </F>
  [Text] Dutch Judges have been in Cyprus investigating 
allegations of drug smuggling involving offshore companies from 
Holland, it was revealed yesterday. 
  Police spokesman Savas Andoniadhis said the judges, who were 
assisted by the Cyprus force, were conducting a general inquiry 
into smuggling. 
  Narcotics and fabrics are understood to have been included 
in 
the investigations. The judges were on the island for ten days. 
  The value of the smuggled goods is believed to be thousands 
of dollars. 
  A seven-member team comprising the judges, lawyers, and tax 
inspectors investigated two unnamed Dutch offshore companies. 
  The companies are believed to have moved huge quantities of 
fabric to Lebanon and Pakistan using documents relating to 
another country. 
  According to reports, members of one offshore company were 
described as owners of boat which was bought with drugs money. 
  A Dutch judge issued a confiscation order on the unnamed 
boat 
and any property gained through smuggling. 

