<H3> <TI>   Officials Claim Rostock `Biggest Center' for Cocaine </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0302171694 Hamburg DPA in German 1536 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0302171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Rostock -- According to the Regional Finance Office 
in Rostock, the port of Rostock has developed into the biggest 
German drug trafficking center for cocaine. Since July 1992, a 
total of 240 kg of cocaine has been impounded in six operations, 
a spokesman of the authority announced today when presenting the 
annual 1993 customs report for Mecklenburg-Western Pomerania. 
Thus, the situation in Rostock is worse than in Hamburg, 
Bremen, and even Antwerp. The drugs have a street value of 
approximately 80 million German marks. In the most recent 
operation this year, in November, police seized 12 kg of cocaine 
aboard the freighter Bille Trop from Columbia. 

</TEXT>

