<H3> <TI>   Riga To Host Baltic Regional Bureau for Drug Control </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0402103494 Tallinn BNS in English 2044 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0402103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] RIGA, Feb 03, BNS - The Latvian capital, Riga, will 
host the office of the Baltic regional bureau for the control of 
narcotic drugs, U.N. expert Dagmar Thomas Halasek told reporters. 
  The bureau's activities will also embrace Lithuania and 
Estonia, Halasek said. The main office will be situated in Riga 
because of the city's advantageous geographical position and the 
successful operation of the Latvian National Drugs Control 
Commission. 
  The bureau will coordinate the efforts of police, customs 
and 
frontier guards to curb the spread of narcotic drugs. 
  Latvia reported 219 criminal cases connected with drugs' 
abuse in 1993, said Vilnis Kipens, a spokesman for the Riga 
Criminal Police Department. In 1993, 47 people died from 
overuse of drugs, the figure increased by 27 death cases 
compared with 1992. 
  Drugs are trafficked to Latvia mainly from Lithuania and the 
Kaliningrad district of Russia, Kipens said. 

</TEXT>

