<H3> <TI>   Pakistan, Iran Reach Agreement on Closer Antinarcotics Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0802162794 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0802162794 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan and Iran have agreed on closer cooperation 
to eliminate the menace of narcotics and to launch [a] campaign 
against trafficking of illicit drugs and psychotropic 
substances. The agreement came at the conclusion of the 
three-day session of the Pakistan-Iran Special Committee on 
Interior and Security in Islamabad today. The Iranian deputy 
interior minister for political and social affairs, Mr. ('Ali 
Reza Tabish), and the federal secretary, interior, Mr. Jamshed 
Barki, signed the agreement. Both sides also discussed in 
detail matters pertaining to expansion of border trade and 
improvement of communication. 

