<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Al-Sallum, 10 Feb (MENA)--Undercover agents at the 
al-Sallum border crossing today seized 8 kg of crude opium oil 
[Zayt al-Afyun al-Kham] in bottles concealed inside the tires of 
a vehicle driving from Libya. 
  The driver, Hafiz 'Abd-al-Sattar Muhammad, said he is 
employed by Ayman Khidr, the proprietor of an import-export firm 
in Alexandria. He added that he took delivery of the vehicle 
from its owner in the Libyan town of Darnah. The owner told him 
he would follow him in three days. 
  Sa'd Mutawalli, chief prosecutor in Marsa Matruh 
Governorate, 
remanded the driver for four days pending investigation and sent 
a specimen of the seized merchandise to the forensic laboratory 
for examination. He also issued instructions to arraign the 
export firm proprietor. 

