<H3> <TI>   Besharati Interviewed on Border Closure, Zahedan Incidents </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802122594 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1030 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802122594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] By closing about 840 km of the country's eastern 
borders against the smugglers, routes used by the 
drug-trafficking convoys from the borders into the country are 
blocked. 
  Interior Minister ['Ali Mohammad] Besharati, in an interview 
with our correspondent, also said: The task of closing the 
borders in the vulnerable areas began from four months ago. The 
job was completed by digging canals of four meters deep and four 
meters wide, erection of many watch towers, and planting of 
mines along the routes used by the drug-trafficking convoys. At 
present there is no possibility of such convoys finding their 
way into the country. 
  About the recent disturbances in Zahedan, which took place 
with provocation of the drug-traffickers, the interior minister 
praised the Muslim and revolutionary people of Zahedan for 
staging a rally on Sunday to condemn the action of these 
saboteurs. He said: The Shiite and Sunni brothers and sisters, 
by staging a march in Zahedan to protest against the 
drug-traffickers, have once again demonstrated their support for 
the Islamic revolution, the esteemed leader, and the president, 
and they have terminated all the conspiracies spread by internal 
and foreign enemies. 

</TEXT>

