<F P=102>  BK0602121794 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 
1100 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0602121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A comprehensive draft antinarcotics law has been 
finalized to replace the existing law to provide death penalty 
and seizure of assets as maximum punishment for those involved 
in drug-related crimes. The federal interior minister, retired 
Major General Nasirullah Babar, told a news conference in 
Islamabad today that the law is likely to be adopted by the 
parliament in a few month's time. He reiterated the commitment 
of the government to eradicate the drug menace from the society. 
The minister said over 64,000 kg of narcotics were seized 
during the 100 days of the present government. 

