<F P=100> WEST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> ITALY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Naples Police Smash Heroin Ring </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0902084094 Paris AFP in English 0300 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0902084094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Naples, Italy, Feb 9 (AFP) -- Police have smashed a 
drug-trafficking ring involving heroin worth 50 billion lire (30 
million dollars) and arrested 42 people, police sources said 
Tuesday [8 February]. 
  A further 28 people already serving prison sentences were 
also said to be implicated in the ring, which came to light 
following confessions by five former members of the Camorra, the 
Neapolitan Mafia. 
  According to the confessions, the drug trafficking was 
controlled by 12 Mafia families headed by boss Raffaele Ascione. 
  Up to 1,000 fixes of heroin a day were being sold by the 
gang. Police did not say if they had seized the drugs. 

</TEXT>

