<H3> <TI>   Drug Addiction in Maritime Kray Far Exceeds National Average </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0802145594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 5 Feb 94 First 
Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM0802145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [INTERFAX report under "From Our Correspondents and News </F>
Agencies" rubric: "Incidence of Drug Addiction in Maritime Kray 
29 Times the Russian Average"] 
  [Text] The scale of the spread of drug addiction in 
Maritime Kray has become socially dangerous in nature. 
  The incidence of this affliction is 29 times the Russian 
average, INTERFAX was informed by the kray internal affairs 
administration. The estimated value of the 1,247 kg of drugs 
seized en route to the black market is over 8 billion rubles. 
During the year the number of drugs-related crimes increased 
22.6 percent. 

</TEXT>

