<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> RUSSIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azeri `Gang' in Vladivostok Arrested in Drug Raid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702065894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0543 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0702065894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yuriy Grachev] </F>
  [Text] Vladivostok February 7 ITAR-TASS -- A gang of Azeris 
suspected of involvement in a variety of crimes was liquidated 
last Friday by the local department in charge of combatting drug 
trafficking. 
  "We planned the operation quite thoroughly to capture all 
members of the gang in one week," said Vladimir Kolosov, chief 
of the Internal Affairs Department of the Maritime Territory. 
  "Ten chieftains of the Azeri diaspora were detained, 
including one criminal authority who controlled the fund which 
provided assistance to criminals and their families." 
  One of the chieftains had on him raw opium and syringes, was 
armed and carried 2,640,000 roubles and 900 U.S. dollars in his 
wallet. 
  Forty Caucasians residing in Vladivostok without proper 
registration were also detained. There was no shooting or 
violence in the course of the operation. 

</TEXT>

