<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> LITHUANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vilnius Police Confiscate Kilogram of Opium, Arrest Three </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0902163694 Vilnius ELTA in Lithuanian 1336 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0902163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius police detained three persons in a city 
apartment where they discovered and confiscated a kilogram of 
opium.... This is the largest amount of narcotic substances, 
worth almost $10,000, that has been detected in Lithuania. Over 
the last year, the police found 663 grams of illegally kept 
opium. According to medical people, opium is the most 
widespread drug in Lithuania. Narcotics are supposed to arrive 
in Lithuania from Asian countries. There are attempts to transit 
drugs through Lithuania as well. While inspecting a passenger 
train in Kybartai recently, customs officers confiscated five 
kilograms of ground poppy heads from three Russian citizens. 
Three Ukrainian residents were found carrying 32 kilograms of 
narcotic substances by car at the Latezeris customs house. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

