<H3> <TI>   Army To Take `More Active Role' Against Drug Trade in Amazon Region </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0192B Brasilia CORREIO BRAZILIENSE in Portuguese 17 Jan 
94 p 8 </F>

<F P=103> 94WD0192B </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia CORREIO BRAZILIENSE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Brazilian Army units in the Amazon Region will take 
a more active role in combating the narcotics traffic. Measures 
toward that end are being developed by the Army General Staff. 
Possible actions include the use of Army helicopters to back up 
the work of the Federal Police. Three aircraft are already 
operating in Manaus at the Military Command of Amazonia. In the 
future, a company of those aircraft will be assigned there, as 
the embryo of a future Helicopter Battalion in that region, Army 
sources say. 

