<F P=100> NEAR EAST &amp; SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> INDIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mandrax Destined for Mozambique Seized at Bombay Dock </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0201B Madras THE HINDU in English 29 Dec 93 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0201B </F>
<F P=104>  Madras THE HINDU </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article: "Narcotics Seizure"] </F>
  [Text] Bombay, Dec. 28. The Narcotics Control Bureau (NCB) 
of Bombay Customs seized 2210 packets of mandrax tablets 
weighing 1435 kg and valued at Rs. 30 crore in the international 
market from a export consignment at Indira dock in South Bombay 
this afternoon. 
  According to NCB sources, the consignment which was marked 
water heaters was to be shipped to Mozambique. Two persons have 
been detained in this connection. 

</TEXT>

