<F P=103> 94WD0201C </F>
<F P=104>  Madras THE HINDU </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article: "Heroin Seized"] </F>
  [Text] Madras, Jan. 7. Heroin, valued at about Rs 3 crores 
in the international market, has been seized by officials of the 
Narcotics Control Bureau (NCB) South Zone, Madras, from two 
gangs of drug traffickers operating independently in Madras and 
Madurai. 
  According to Mr P.V.K. Reddy, Deputy Director of the NCB, 
South Zone, Madras, on the basis of specific intelligence, the 
officers intercepted a private omni bus near the Tambaram 
checkpost on Wednesday and seized 2 kg of high quality heroin 
from two passengers. The bus was bound for Tirunelveli. The 
heroin was concealed in the false bottom of two zipper rexin 
bags. It was to be exported from the southern coast to Sri Lanka. 

