<H3> <TI>   Six Killed in IRGC Clashes With Drug Smugglers in Kerman </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1202110894 Tehran KEYHAN in Persian 2 Feb 94 p 15 </F>
<F P=103> NC1202110894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran KEYHAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Combatants of the 41st Sarallah Army of the Islamic 
Revolution Guards Corps' [IRGC] ground forces carried out a 
successful operation during which six drug convoys were 
destroyed in Kerman's Anduhjerd region and in the hard to reach 
heights. 
  The IRGC public relations office reports that during these 
operations, which were code named "The Birth of Mahdi, May God 
Hasten His Advent," the IRGC's 41st Sarallah Army engaged in 
several hours of clashes with drug smugglers and disbanded the 
convoys of 'Isa, Javad, and Shamshir Shahbakhsh and also 
inflicted heavy blows on three other convoys that belonged to 
the Shahbakhshi's. The report adds that the operations were 
supported by the Kerman Army Air Corps and that six of the 
traffickers were killed and 10 were wounded in the clashes. 
  Also, during the operations 32 sacks of drugs weighing 241 
kg 
were found and five vehicles, 30 motorbikes, and 40 light 
weapons and ammunition were confiscated. 

</TEXT>

