<H3> <TI>   Heroin Smuggled in Boots Seized, Three Arrested </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WB0006A Peshawar MASHRIQ in Urdu 17 Sep 93 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> 94WB0006A </F>
<F P=104>  Peshawar MASHRIQ </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [News Report: "Three Smugglers Arrested for Attempting To </F>
Smuggle Narcotics in Shoes; Those Arrested Include a Brother and 
Sister; the Police Have Charged the Accused and Started 
Investigaton."] 
  [Text] Peshawar (Staff Reporter): The Narcotics Control 
Board carried out raids in Peshawar Bannu and foiled attempts to 
smuggle narcotics worth large sums of money. Three smugglers 
were arrested including a brother and sister. The suspects have 
been charged in the police stations concerned. According to 
details received, Nizamud din, a resident of Tehkal Payan, hid a 
half kilogram of heroin in his boots and arrived at Bara bus 
stand on GT road with the intention of travelling to a certain 
destination. An informant tipped off the Narcotics Control Board 
and the Board agents arrived at the bus stand and surrounded the 
suspect. They searched the man and found heroin hidden in his 
boots. Agents of the Bannu narcotics control board raided a bus 
bound for Laki and seized 2 kilograms of opium and four 
kilograms of marijuana from a brother and sister, named Rozena 
and Mohammad Ayaz, both residents of Char Sada. 

</TEXT>

