<F P=101> NIGERIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senior NDLEA Officers `Discharged,' Probe Continues </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB1602195694 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 1500 GMT 
16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB1602195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] All the senior officers of the National Drug law 
Enforcement Agency, summoned by the Currency and Miscellaneous 
Offenses Tribunal in connection with the missing sachets of 
heroin, have been discharged by the tribunal. They will now 
face a ministerial commission of inquiry set up to probe the 
agency. In her ruling today, the chairman of the tribunal, Mrs. 
Justice Olufumi Layo Oniokpako, said she agreed with the defense 
counsel that the officers be discharged in order not to hinder 
the progress of the ministerial inquiry. She, however, ordered 
that the findings of the probe panel be submitted to the 
tribunal. The officers include the director general of the 
agency, Dr. Yusuf Digbai. 

</TEXT>

