<H3> <TI>   DEC Announces 29 Drug-Related Arrests During Nov-Dec </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0195A Lusaka TIMES OF ZAMBIA in English 25 Dec 93 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0195A </F>
<F P=104>  Lusaka TIMES OF ZAMBIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Excerpt] The Drug Enforcement Commission (DEC) has 
arrested 22 Zambians and seven foreigners for trafficking in 
narcotic drugs with a total street value of K438.5m between 
November 1 and December 24. 
  Of the 29 people arrested, 20 had been successfully 
prosecuted and convicted, six were awaiting final completion of 
their cases and only one was discharged. 
  Among foreigners who had drugs ranging from cannabis to 
heroin were two Guineans, one Namibian, one South African, one 
Tanzanian, one Zimbabwean and a Malian. 
  A statement released by the commission in Lusaka yesterday 
shows the drugs seized by officers were mandrax worth 
K174,954,600, heroin valued at K185,062,500, cannabis--K79,700 
and cannabis seeds, worth K7,810,000. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

