<H3> <TI>   Police Arrest American, 3 Nigerians, Seize 4 Kg of Heroin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1802164794 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 18 Feb 94 p 11 </F>
<F P=103> AU1802164794 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [APA Report: "Heroin Ring Smashed, Three Nigerians </F>
Arrested"] 
  [Text] Vienna -- An American drug courier was arrested 
when he entered Austria, and 4 kg of heroin was seized. 
Officials of the Schwechat drug police thought the route of the 
24-year-old U.S. citizen James R. highly unusual. The man 
arrived on Aeroflot flight SU 261 from Brazil via Moscow at 
Vienna's Schwechat Airport at noon on Wednesday [16 February]. 
During a careful check, 4 kg of heroin was discovered in the 
false bottom of his bag. 
  When he was interrogated, James R. claimed that he was only 
the courier, and that he had received the drugs in Brazil. His 
statements led to the arrest of three Nigerians in Vienna on the 
same day. For technical reasons, the police declined on 
Thursday [17 February] to disclose their names and the functions 
within the drug ring. 
  Yesterday the fingerprints of the arrested drug dealers were 
checked. Results are expected today, Friday. Moreover, an 
exact analysis of the impounded drugs is not yet available. 

</TEXT>

