<H3> <TI>   Moscow MVD Carry Out Drug Bust </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1602105594 Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA in Russian 15 Feb 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM1602105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from the "Inform" roundup: "`Big Fish' Comes Down </F>
From a High"] 
  [Text] A targeted drug-busting operation was carried out 
last week by staff from the Moscow Internal Affairs Main 
Administration. They uncovered three opium manufacturing 
laboratories and confiscated 150 kg of poppy haulms, almost 1.5 
liters of opium solution, and a Kalashnikov rifle. The 
operatives discovered the largest haul at a house on Kerch 
Street: A certain Gubanov was found in possession of 97 kg of 
poppy haulms. 
  But it was detectives from the regional administration for 
combating organized crime who provided the high point of the 
operation. They basically brought to an end the "high" enjoyed 
by a Georgian criminal community resident in the "Rossiyanochka" 
Hotel on Leninskiy Prospekt. Seven addicts were caught 
red-handed. 

</TEXT>

